<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0314 </DOCNO><TEXT>The specific features of electron low-energy states in ionic-molecularcrystals have been considered using alkali metal nitrates as an example.The band structure model including the free anion MO levels located atthe forbidden band is suggested. In terms of this model the localizationconditions of excitations, electrons and holes on the lattice anion siteare speculated. It has been concluded that it is an anion sublatticealone that participates in alkali metal nitrate radiolysis.</TEXT></DOC>